Guy's an animal.

11:31.316 --> 11:32.582
Are you crazy?

11:32.584 --> 11:34.317
You lost $50?

11:34.319 --> 11:36.623
Dolores, please.

11:38.257 --> 11:39.558
I ate 26.

11:44.363 --> 11:47.097
You are so lucky.

11:47.099 --> 11:48.465
You know that?
<font color="#ff00ff">(TONY CHUCKLES)</font>

11:48.467 --> 11:50.233
Rent is due on Monday.

11:50.235 --> 11:51.301
<font color="#ff00ff">(CHUCKLES)</font>

11:51.303 --> 11:54.306
<font color="#ff00ff">(PHONE RINGING)</font>

11:55.340 --> 11:56.575
You gonna get that?

11:57.677 --> 11:59.242
<font color="#ff00ff">(SIGHS)</font>

11:59.244 --> 12:01.344
Yeah?
<font color="#ff8000">JULES</font>: Hey, Lip.

12:01.346 --> 12:03.380
Some guy called over here.
A doctor.

12:03.382 --> 12:05.215
He's looking for a driver.

12:05.217 --> 12:07.150
You interested?
Yeah.

12:07.152 --> 12:09.720
They're interviewing guys
tomorrow afternoon.

12:09.722 --> 12:14.725
The address is, uh,
8817th Avenue.

12:14.727 --> 12:16.627
2:15.

12:16.629 --> 12:18.631
<font color="#ff00ff">(MUSIC PLAYING)</font>

12:31.711 --> 12:34.079
<font color="#ff00ff">(MUSIC PLAYING)</font>

12:36.381 --> 12:38.348
Hey. Excuse me.

12:38.350 --> 12:40.150
We're not open right now,
but you're welcome

12:40.152 --> 12:42.185
to purchase tickets
to tonight's performance.

12:42.187 --> 12:43.353
Nah, that's all right.

12:43.355 --> 12:45.656
I, uh... I think
I got the wrong address,

12:45.658 --> 12:48.425
but, uh, is there
a doctor's office in here?

12:48.427 --> 12:49.760
A doctor's office?

12:49.762 --> 12:51.494
Dr. Shirley?

12:51.496 --> 12:53.229
You have the correct address.

12:53.231 --> 12:55.434
Dr. Shirley lives upstairs,
above the Hall.

12:59.237 --> 13:01.204
<font color="#ff00ff">(SIGHS)</font>

13:01.206 --> 13:02.675
How you doing?

13:12.584 --> 13:13.718
<font color="#ff00ff">(CLEARS THROAT)</font>

13:13.720 --> 13:15.454
I'm here for the driver job.

13:16.488 --> 13:18.256
Tony Lip.

13:19.324 --> 13:21.692
No Tony Lip.

13:21.694 --> 13:24.194
No, I should be on there.

13:24.196 --> 13:26.363
Uh...

13:26.365 --> 13:30.400
no, um, I have a Tony Val...
Valle-la-la...

13:30.402 --> 13:32.268
Vallelonga. Yeah.

13:32.270 --> 13:34.605
That's me.

13:34.607 --> 13:36.272
Fill it out while you wait.

13:36.274 --> 13:37.474
What?

13:37.476 --> 13:39.542
Fill it out while you wait.

13:39.544 --> 13:41.480
Oh. Yeah.
<font color="#ff00ff">(SNAPS FINGERS)</font>

13:48.353 --> 13:50.155
<font color="#ff00ff">(TONY GRUNTS)</font>

14:03.636 --> 14:05.303
Have a seat.

14:18.017 --> 14:21.186
<font color="#ff00ff">(BELLS CHIMING IN DISTANCE)</font>

14:23.856 --> 14:27.024
<font color="#ff00ff">(DISTANT DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES)</font>

14:27.026 --> 14:30.195
<font color="#ff00ff">(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)</font>

14:33.465 --> 14:36.399
Mr. Vallelonga.
Sorry to keep you waiting.

14:36.401 --> 14:37.768
Oh.

14:37.770 --> 14:39.335
<font color="#ff00ff">(TONY GRUNTS)</font>

14:39.337 --> 14:40.871
I'm Dr. Donald Shirley.

14:40.873 --> 14:42.606
Tony.

14:42.608 --> 14:45.410
Yes. Please sit down.

14:48.047 --> 14:50.815
Some place you got here.
<font color="#ff00ff">(CHUCKLES)</font>

14:50.817 --> 14:52.850
Are them horns real?

14:52.852 --> 14:55.454
Elephant tusks, yes.

14:56.521 --> 14:57.822
What about that?

14:57.824 --> 14:59.458
Is that a molar?

15:00.793 --> 15:02.292
A what?

15:02.294 --> 15:04.594
A molar, a-a shark tooth.

15:04.596 --> 15:07.064
Or a tiger's, maybe.

15:07.066 --> 15:09.633
It was a gift.

15:09.635 --> 15:12.603
I thought, uh... I thought
I was going to an office.

15:12.605 --> 15:15.505
They said a doctor
needed a driver.

15:15.507 --> 15:16.841
That's all they told you?

15:16.843 --> 15:18.575
Yeah.
<font color="#ff00ff">(CHUCKLES)</font>

15:18.577 --> 15:22.512
Actually, it's a bit more
complicated than that.

15:22.514 --> 15:24.717
Have you ever driven
professionally before?

15:25.752 --> 15:27.550
Yeah. Sanitation.

15:27.552 --> 15:29.319
Garbage trucks.

15:29.321 --> 15:31.889
Plus, I drive my boss home
at night.

15:31.891 --> 15:33.724
But I can drive anything.

15:33.726 --> 15:35.793
Limos. Tow trucks.

15:35.795 --> 15:37.494
Snowplows. Whatever.

15:37.496 --> 15:38.662
I see.

15:38.664 --> 15:40.597
What other experience
do you have?

15:40.599 --> 15:42.332
I worked a lot of joints.

15:42.334 --> 15:44.602
Wagon Wheel,
Peppermint Lounge, Copa.

15:44.604 --> 15:46.402
In what capacity?

15:46.404 --> 15:47.605
What do you mean?

15:47.607 --> 15:49.539
What did you do there?

15:49.541 --> 15:51.276
Uh...

15:52.377 --> 15:53.944
Public relations.

15:53.946 --> 15:57.715
Well, first of all, Tony,
I'm not a medical doctor.

15:57.717 --> 15:58.916
I'm a musician.

15:58.918 --> 16:01.351
You mean, like, songs?

16:01.353 --> 16:02.585
Yes.

16:02.587 --> 16:04.554
And I'm about to embark
on a concert tour,

16:04.556 --> 16:06.489
the majority of which
will be down south.

16:06.491 --> 16:07.725
Atlantic City.

16:07.727 --> 16:08.893
No.

16:08.895 --> 16:10.560
The Deep South.

16:10.562 --> 16:12.495
First, we're starting
in the Midwest,

16:12.497 --> 16:13.898
and then we're taking
a hard left.

16:13.900 --> 16:15.900
Kentucky, North Carolina,
Tennessee,

16:15.902 --> 16:17.868
and on down through the Delta.

16:17.870 --> 16:20.938
Do you foresee any issues
in working for a black man?

16:20.940 --> 16:23.140
No.

16:23.142 --> 16:24.708
No, no, no.

16:24.710 --> 16:26.777
It was just the other day,
me and the wife

16:26.779 --> 16:28.815
had a couple of colored guys
over at the house.

16:30.750 --> 16:32.850
For-for drinks.

16:32.852 --> 16:34.417
Hmm. I see.

16:34.419 --> 16:35.585
You're married.

16:35.587 --> 16:37.890
Yeah. Two kids.

16:39.725 --> 16:42.492
I'm not sure this is the
proper job for a married man.

16:42.494 --> 16:44.494
Why? Are we bringing broads?

16:44.496 --> 16:47.965
My point is we'll be gone
for eight straight weeks.

16:47.967 --> 16:50.634
No breaks,
right up until Christmas.

16:50.636 --> 16:52.970
You're quite sure you can leave
your family for that long?

16:52.972 --> 16:54.839
Depends what you're paying.

16:54.841 --> 16:56.874
A hundred dollars a week,
plus room and board.

16:56.876 --> 16:57.975
<font color="#ff8000">TONY</font>: Hmm.

16:57.977 --> 17:00.510
But let me be crystal clear.

17:00.512 --> 17:02.478
I'm not just hiring a chauffeur.

17:02.480 --> 17:05.616
I need someone
who can handle my itinerary.

17:05.617 --> 17:08.451
Be a personal assistant.
I need a valet.

17:08.453 --> 17:11.924
I need someone who can launder
my clothes and shine my shoes.

17:13.992 --> 17:15.862
Good luck, Doc.

17:18.563 --> 17:19.866
Tony.

17:24.804 --> 17:26.770
I had my record label
ask around town

17:26.771 --> 17:28.706
to find me the right man.

17:28.708 --> 17:31.376
Your name came up
more than once.

17:32.645 --> 17:35.646
You've impressed several people
with your...

17:35.648 --> 17:37.717
innate ability
to handle trouble.

17:38.918 --> 17:40.851
And that is why I called
and inquired

17:40.853 --> 17:42.822
about your availability.

17:45.858 --> 17:47.490
Okay, here's the deal.

17:47.492 --> 17:49.525
I got no problem
being on the road with you.

17:49.527 --> 17:50.661
But I ain't no butler.

17:50.663 --> 17:52.562
I ain't ironing no shirts,

17:52.564 --> 17:53.931
and I'm not polishing
nobody's shoes.

17:53.933 --> 17:56.233
You need somebody to get you
from point A to point B?

17:56.235 --> 17:57.635
You need someone to make sure

17:57.637 --> 17:58.802
there's no problems
along the way?

17:58.804 --> 18:00.804
And believe me,
you and the Deep South,

18:00.806 --> 18:02.640
there's gonna be problems.

18:02.642 --> 18:03.908
So, if you want me,

18:03.910 --> 18:05.943
it's a buck and a quarter
a week.

18:05.945 --> 18:08.544
Or go hire that little Chink
just pranced out of here.

18:08.546 --> 18:10.582
See how far you get.

18:12.018 --> 18:15.551
Well, Mr. Vallelonga,

18:15.553 --> 18:17.888
thank you for stopping by.

18:17.890 --> 18:19.892
<font color="#ff00ff">(MUSIC PLAYING)</font>

18:22.560 --> 18:25.463
<font color="#ff00ff">(QUIET CHATTER)</font>

18:30.069 --> 18:32.069
Hey, Bobby.

18:32.071 --> 18:33.971
Give me a Rheingold.

18:33.973 --> 18:35.841
Ice cold.

18:44.817 --> 18:45.851
Mr. Tony.

18:47.552 --> 18:49.519
Augie asking about you.

18:49.521 --> 18:50.955
<font color="#ff00ff">(BANGING ON BAR)</font>

18:50.957 --> 18:52.690
Come on!
I'm dying of thirst over here.

18:52.692 --> 18:53.724
Shut up!

18:53.726 --> 18:55.560
I'm talking.

18:58.297 --> 18:59.663
When?

18:59.665 --> 19:01.867
Now. He in his box.

19:22.888 --> 19:24.790
<font color="#ff00ff">(KNOCKS)</font>

19:27.994 --> 19:29.494
Tony Lip.

19:31.130 --> 19:33.030
What the hell happened
at the Copa?

19:33.032 --> 19:34.967
I hear you almost split
a guy's face open.

19:36.135 --> 19:38.869
That guy you hit, Mikey Cerrone,

19:38.871 --> 19:40.873
part of Charlie the Hand's crew.

19:42.041 --> 19:44.043
Guess he should have
known better.

19:46.112 --> 19:48.345
<font color="#ff00ff">(AUGIE SIGHS)</font>

19:48.347 --> 19:50.647
Hand asked me to look into it.

19:50.649 --> 19:52.649
I spoke to Podell.

19:52.651 --> 19:55.855
Whole thing was, uh,
over a piece of ass, right?

19:56.989 --> 19:58.822
Yeah.

19:58.824 --> 20:02.592
Beef like that should never
happen inside the club.

20:02.594 --> 20:04.795
They were out of line.

20:04.797 --> 20:06.799
So we squashed it.

20:08.801 --> 20:11.769
You, uh, looking to earn
a little extra <i>scharole?</i>

20:11.771 --> 20:14.671
I can keep you busy
while the Copa is down.

20:14.673 --> 20:15.975
What do I gotta do?

20:17.943 --> 20:19.979
Things.

20:22.648 --> 20:24.214
Appreciate it, but, uh,

20:24.216 --> 20:26.717
I want to spend some time
with the family.

20:26.719 --> 20:28.619
<font color="#ff8000">AUGIE</font>: Don't be stupid.

20:28.621 --> 20:31.722
You make yourself a few extra
bucks, you buy something nice

20:31.724 --> 20:33.991
for that pretty little wife
of yours.

20:33.993 --> 20:35.961
Hmm.

20:38.064 --> 20:39.997
Nah, I'm good.

20:39.999 --> 20:41.967
I'm flush right now.

20:43.035 --> 20:47.805
<i><font color="#ffff00">♪</font> So long, Lover's Island</i>

20:47.807 --> 20:50.074
<i><font color="#ffff00">♪</font> Dee
<font color="#ffff00">♪</font> Dee-ooh</i>

20:50.076 --> 20:52.676
<i><font color="#ffff00">♪</font> Ee, ah, ooh, ay...</i>

20:52.678 --> 20:55.145
<font color="#ff00ff">(SONG CONTINUES QUIETLY)</font>

20:55.147 --> 20:56.980
Here's 50.

20:56.982 --> 20:59.952
Here. Pay me 60 by New Year's,
you get it back.

21:02.922 --> 21:05.155
Hey, Lip.

21:05.157 --> 21:07.124
Everything okay?

21:07.126 --> 21:09.862
What, you got
beak trouble, Charlie?

21:10.996 --> 21:13.697
Mind your business.

21:13.699 --> 21:14.998
<i><font color="#ffff00">♪</font> Lover's Island...</i>

21:15.000 --> 21:16.433
<font color="#ff00ff">(DOOR OPENS)</font>

21:16.435 --> 21:18.135
So, come on.
I'm dying to hear.

21:18.137 --> 21:19.870
What happened
with the doctor interview?

21:19.872 --> 21:21.872
He ain't a real doctor.

21:21.874 --> 21:23.273
He's a piano player.

21:23.275 --> 21:25.142
Well, I don't understand.

21:25.144 --> 21:27.010
Why did they say
that he was a doctor?

21:27.012 --> 21:29.146
I don't know.
I think he's, like,

21:29.148 --> 21:31.682
a doctor of, uh,
piano playing or something.

21:31.684 --> 21:33.016
You can be that?

21:33.018 --> 21:34.685
I guess.

21:34.687 --> 21:36.954
He lives on top
of Carnegie Hall.

21:36.956 --> 21:38.822
You should've seen
this place, Dee.

21:38.824 --> 21:41.225
It was filled with statues
and all kinds of fancy crap.

21:41.227 --> 21:43.760
And he was sitting on top
of a friggin' throne

21:43.762 --> 21:46.196
all dressed up like, uh, like
the king of the jungle bunnies.

21:46.198 --> 21:49.068
He's colored?

21:50.169 --> 21:51.869
<font color="#ff00ff">(SCOFFS SOFTLY)</font>

21:51.871 --> 21:53.904
Well, you wouldn't last
a week with him.

21:53.906 --> 21:56.473
For the right money, I would.

21:56.475 --> 21:57.774
<font color="#ff00ff">(TONY SNORING)</font>

21:57.776 --> 21:59.778
<font color="#ff00ff">(PHONE RINGING)</font>

22:03.182 --> 22:04.715
<font color="#ff00ff">(GROANS)</font>

22:04.717 --> 22:06.049
<font color="#ff00ff">(SIGHS)</font>

22:06.051 --> 22:08.485
Yeah.

22:08.487 --> 22:10.087
Oh.

22:10.089 --> 22:12.890
Look... <font color="#ff00ff">(CLEARS THROAT)</font>

22:12.892 --> 22:14.758
Really?

22:14.760 --> 22:15.959
Uh, okay.
You okay?

22:15.961 --> 22:17.261
Okay, hang on a sec.

22:17.263 --> 22:21.498
It's, uh, Dr. Shirley,
the piano guy.

22:21.500 --> 22:23.300
He wants to talk to you.

22:23.302 --> 22:24.968
Me?
Yeah.

22:24.970 --> 22:26.770
What? No.

22:26.772 --> 22:28.071
Come on.

22:28.073 --> 22:29.306
Take it.
No. Tony...

22:29.308 --> 22:30.943
Just... just talk.

22:34.079 --> 22:35.814
Hello?

22:37.082 --> 22:39.183
<font color="#ff00ff">(CHUCKLES)</font>
Uh, good morning, Doctor.

22:39.185 --> 22:41.220
It's nice to talk to you.

22:46.091 --> 22:48.928
Well, uh, yes,
that is a long time.

22:51.864 --> 22:53.165
It is.

22:54.967 --> 22:57.067
Yes. I'm sure.

22:57.069 --> 22:59.002
<font color="#ff00ff">(FAINTLY OVER PHONE)</font>
Thank you.

22:59.004 --> 23:01.205
Thank you for calling.

23:01.207 --> 23:02.841
Bye, now.

23:05.110 --> 23:07.079
What'd he say?

23:08.314 --> 23:10.347
He wanted to know if I'd be okay

23:10.349 --> 23:15.219
with him taking my husband away
from his family for two months.

23:15.221 --> 23:18.724
He said he'd pay you
what you asked for.

23:21.093 --> 23:22.761
<font color="#ff00ff">(TONY GRUNTS)</font>

23:23.796 --> 23:25.331
Hey.
Hmm?

23:27.132 --> 23:29.166
It's good money.

23:29.168 --> 23:31.036
We need it.

23:33.172 --> 23:37.042
Can't be eating 26 hot dogs
every day.

23:38.877 --> 23:41.378
I know.
<font color="#ff00ff">(SNIFFLES)</font>

23:41.380 --> 23:44.718
I told him it was okay
for you to go.

23:46.919 --> 23:49.219
All right, hey, look, so here's
the first half of your pay.

23:49.221 --> 23:51.154
You're gonna get the rest
when the tour's over.

23:51.156 --> 23:52.889
No, I gotta get paid every week.

23:52.891 --> 23:54.891
Sorry. That's not how
the record company does it.

23:54.893 --> 23:57.060
We got to have some guarantee
you're gonna finish the job.

23:57.062 --> 23:59.963
Why wouldn't I finish the job?
I took it, didn't I?

23:59.965 --> 24:03.300
Well, then we got nothing
to worry about.

24:03.302 --> 24:05.969
Here's the deal,
Mr. Vallelonga.

24:05.971 --> 24:08.338
Okay, it's your job to get Don
to all his tour dates on time.

24:08.340 --> 24:09.873
Now, if he misses any shows,

24:09.875 --> 24:11.074
you're not getting
your back end.

24:11.076 --> 24:13.277
He's not gonna miss any show.
Good.

24:13.279 --> 24:16.046
Oh, you're gonna need this.

24:16.048 --> 24:18.115
Now, this is the book
I was telling you about.

24:18.117 --> 24:20.183
Now, sometimes you guys
are staying in the same hotel,

24:20.185 --> 24:22.319
sometimes you're not.

24:22.321 --> 24:24.921
<font color="#ff8000">TONY</font>: Oh, yeah, the...
Yeah, yeah.

24:24.923 --> 24:28.091
All right, don't let me down.
Let's go.

24:28.093 --> 24:30.095
<font color="#ff00ff">(MUSIC PLAYING)</font>

24:34.900 --> 24:37.100
<i>Madonne,</i> is this the new one?

24:37.102 --> 24:39.102
Yeah, the record company
rented it.

24:39.104 --> 24:40.871
It's nice, huh?
Beautiful.

24:40.873 --> 24:42.472
So, what'd my sister have to say

24:42.474 --> 24:44.474
about you being gone
for three weeks?

24:44.476 --> 24:46.877
Eight weeks.
<font color="#ff00ff">(SCOFFS)</font>

24:46.879 --> 24:48.646
Ten to one,
you slap this moolie out,

24:48.648 --> 24:51.948
you come home in under a month.
<font color="#ff00ff">(SPEAKS ITALIAN)</font>

24:51.950 --> 24:53.651
Come here.
All right, boys, huddle up.

24:53.653 --> 24:55.952
Say good-bye to your father.
Frankie, Nicky. Come here.

24:55.954 --> 24:57.087
All right.

24:57.089 --> 24:58.955
You gonna be good boys?
Uh-huh.

24:58.957 --> 25:00.390
You'll listen to your mother?
Mm-hmm.

25:00.392 --> 25:02.259
Yeah? All right, give me a kiss.

25:02.261 --> 25:05.195
I'm counting on you.

25:05.197 --> 25:07.833
Don't go too far.
We won't.

25:10.235 --> 25:13.303
Did you go to the AAA for the maps?
Yes.

25:13.305 --> 25:15.972
No. I mean, the record
companies gave me the maps

25:15.974 --> 25:17.976
and the itinerary,
and this thing.

25:19.244 --> 25:21.345
<i>The Negro Motorist's Green Book.</i>

25:21.347 --> 25:24.348
Yeah, it lists all the places
coloreds can stay down south.

25:24.350 --> 25:27.250
Like a... you know,
traveling while black.

25:27.252 --> 25:30.120
"Traveling while black"?
Yeah, if you're black

25:30.122 --> 25:31.988
and you gotta travel,
for some reason.

25:31.990 --> 25:34.991
Got a special book for that?
I guess.

25:34.993 --> 25:37.194
Did you pack the iron?
I ain't lugging no iron, Dee.

25:37.196 --> 25:39.329
Come on.
How are you gonna press your pants, Tony?

25:39.331 --> 25:41.998
I'll put 'em under the mattress.

25:42.000 --> 25:44.067
I want you to write me a letter.

25:44.069 --> 25:46.136
Every chance you get.
I can't write letters.

25:46.138 --> 25:47.705
Yes, you can.

25:47.707 --> 25:49.272
I can't write.
Take you five minutes.

25:49.274 --> 25:50.407
Promise me.
It's embarrassing.

25:50.409 --> 25:52.209
It ain't gonna be no good.

25:52.211 --> 25:54.978
It's a lot cheaper than
calling long-distance, Tony.

25:54.980 --> 25:56.980
Promise me you're gonna write.

25:56.982 --> 25:58.852
I promise.

26:00.552 --> 26:02.552
Dee, put this in a bank today.

26:02.554 --> 26:04.488
It's half my pay.

26:04.490 --> 26:06.523
Oh. Here.
There's a couple of sandwiches

26:06.525 --> 26:08.425
for you and Dr. Shirley.

26:08.427 --> 26:09.493
Thanks.

26:09.495 --> 26:11.027
Be careful.

26:11.029 --> 26:13.430
I will.
I love you.

26:13.432 --> 26:15.098
I love you, too, baby.

26:15.100 --> 26:17.970
<font color="#ff00ff">("A LETTER FROM MY BABY"
BY TIMMY SHAW PLAYING)</font>

26:19.338 --> 26:21.338
You better be home
for Christmas,

26:21.340 --> 26:23.242
