42:24.203 --> 42:25.535
<i><font color="#ffff00">♪</font> Lucille...</i>

42:25.537 --> 42:29.239
I don't know.
Sounds fairly complicated.

42:29.241 --> 42:31.942
Got that right.

42:31.944 --> 42:34.444
So, where did this "Tony
the Lip" moniker come from?

42:34.446 --> 42:37.447
<font color="#ff00ff">(CHUCKLES)</font>
It's not Tony the Lip.

42:37.449 --> 42:40.117
It's Tony Lip. One word.

42:40.119 --> 42:42.452
I got it when I was kid,
'cause my friend said

42:42.454 --> 42:45.255
I was the best bullshit artist
in the Bronx.

42:45.257 --> 42:47.290
<font color="#ff00ff">(CHUCKLES)</font>
Why are you smiling?

42:47.292 --> 42:49.092
What do you mean?

42:49.094 --> 42:51.228
It doesn't bother you
that your friends,

42:51.230 --> 42:53.563
the people closest to you,
consider you a liar?

42:53.565 --> 42:55.198
Who said "liar"?

42:55.200 --> 42:57.334
I said "bullshit artist."

42:57.336 --> 42:59.069
And what's the difference?

42:59.071 --> 43:01.338
'Cause I don't lie. Ever.

43:01.340 --> 43:03.507
I'm just good
at talking people into...

43:03.509 --> 43:06.009
you know, doing things
they don't want to do.

43:06.011 --> 43:08.178
By bullshitting them.

43:08.180 --> 43:10.180
And you're proud of that?

43:10.182 --> 43:11.515
Well, it got me this job.

43:11.517 --> 43:14.117
<i><font color="#ffff00">♪</font> Lucille, please don't...</i>

43:14.119 --> 43:17.053
CHUBBY CHECKER: <i><font color="#ffff00">♪</font> Baby, baby,
baby, baby, take it easy... <font color="#ffff00">♪</font></i>

43:17.055 --> 43:18.588
Wait a minute.
You're full of shit.

43:18.590 --> 43:20.223
You never heard
of Chubby Checker?

43:20.225 --> 43:22.058
Of course I've heard of him.

43:22.060 --> 43:24.060
I've just never heard his music before.
I mean...

43:24.062 --> 43:26.329
But I like this.
This is nice.

43:26.331 --> 43:28.331
He's got a silky voice,
very smooth.

43:28.333 --> 43:30.066
Yeah, he's terrific.

43:30.068 --> 43:32.068
This is what everybody's
dancing to now.

43:32.070 --> 43:33.670
This stuff...
Eyes on the road, Tony.

43:35.240 --> 43:37.107
<font color="#ff8000">ARETHA FRANKLIN</font>:
<i><font color="#ffff00">♪</font> Baby, here I am...</i>

43:37.109 --> 43:38.442
You know this song.

43:38.444 --> 43:40.177
I don't think so, no.

43:40.179 --> 43:42.579
How could you
not know this music?

43:42.581 --> 43:44.782
Aretha Franklin.

43:44.784 --> 43:47.317
Chubby Checker,
Little Richard, Sam Cooke.

43:47.319 --> 43:51.021
I mean, come on, Doc.
These are your people.

43:51.023 --> 43:53.557
<i><font color="#ffff00">♪</font> And it won't be long</i>

43:53.559 --> 43:55.494
<i><font color="#ffff00">♪</font> No, it won't be long...</i>

44:04.369 --> 44:07.103
Do you want anything?
I'm getting a pack of smokes.

44:07.105 --> 44:08.974
No, thank you.

44:11.543 --> 44:13.278
<font color="#ff00ff">(SIGHS)</font>

44:24.223 --> 44:25.457
<font color="#ff00ff">(SIGHS)</font>

44:33.565 --> 44:35.434
<font color="#ff00ff">(BELLS JINGLING)</font>
<font color="#ff00ff">(SIGHS)</font>

44:36.468 --> 44:38.201
<font color="#ff00ff">(OLEG SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)</font>

44:38.203 --> 44:40.237
<font color="#ff8000">OLEG</font>: Grabbed the rock
and put it in his pocket.

44:40.239 --> 44:41.606
Thank you, Oleg.

44:41.608 --> 44:43.173
Nice turtleneck.

44:43.175 --> 44:44.543
Way to mix it up.

44:47.412 --> 44:49.412
Got you an apple, Doc.

44:49.414 --> 44:52.084
<font color="#ff00ff">(ENGINE STARTS)</font>
<font color="#ff00ff">(TONY GRUNTS)</font>

44:54.654 --> 44:58.223
Before we pull out, Tony,
we need to have a talk.

44:59.424 --> 45:00.858
Yeah?

45:00.860 --> 45:02.592
Oleg told me what you did.

45:02.594 --> 45:04.261
What'd I do?

45:04.263 --> 45:06.496
You stole a jade stone
from the store.

45:06.498 --> 45:08.633
No, I didn't.
He watched you do it.

45:08.635 --> 45:10.534
I didn't steal no stone.

45:10.536 --> 45:12.469
You picked it up
and put it in your pocket.

45:12.471 --> 45:14.304
I picked up a rock
off of the ground.

45:14.306 --> 45:15.372
I didn't steal from a box.

45:15.374 --> 45:17.507
Now, why would you pick up
a rock off the ground?

45:17.509 --> 45:19.376
I don't know.

45:19.378 --> 45:21.378
'Cause it ain't stealing.

45:21.380 --> 45:22.579
It's just a regular rock.

45:22.581 --> 45:24.548
And why would you want
a regular rock?

45:24.550 --> 45:26.182
To have.

45:26.184 --> 45:27.885
For luck, maybe.

45:27.887 --> 45:29.185
A lucky rock.

45:29.187 --> 45:31.189
Yeah.
Let me see it.

45:36.161 --> 45:37.496
<font color="#ff00ff">(SIGHS)</font>

45:42.534 --> 45:44.902
Mm-mm.

45:44.904 --> 45:47.337
Take it back and pay for it.

45:47.339 --> 45:49.205
<font color="#ff00ff">(MUTTERS IN ITALIAN)</font>

45:49.207 --> 45:51.341
I told you that kraut
was a snake.

45:51.343 --> 45:53.510
Rats me out for something
I didn't even do!

45:53.512 --> 45:55.613
Pay for the stone, Tony;
You'll feel better.

45:55.615 --> 45:58.716
I feel fine. And I ain't paying
for no regular rock

45:58.718 --> 46:01.284
I found in the dirt.

46:01.286 --> 46:04.487
Do not drive, Mr. Vallelonga.

46:04.489 --> 46:06.657
<font color="#ff00ff">(TONY SIGHS)</font>

46:06.659 --> 46:08.661
Put it back.

46:15.567 --> 46:19.237
<font color="#ff00ff">(MUSIC PLAYING)</font>

46:30.282 --> 46:32.617
<font color="#ff00ff">(STARTS ENGINE)</font>

46:32.619 --> 46:35.218
Feel better?
No.

46:35.220 --> 46:37.955
If you'd like, Tony,
I'd happily buy you the stone.

46:37.957 --> 46:41.391
Don't bother.
You took all the fun out of it.

46:41.393 --> 46:44.596
<font color="#ff00ff">(MUSIC PLAYING)</font>

46:50.502 --> 46:54.172
<font color="#ff00ff">(CELLO PLAYING MINOR-KEY
CLASSICAL MUSIC)</font>

47:14.359 --> 47:16.361
<font color="#ff00ff">(MUSIC PLAYING)</font>

47:17.997 --> 47:20.563
Excuse me. Sir.

47:20.565 --> 47:22.365
I'm with the band.

47:22.367 --> 47:23.500
You're all set up.

47:23.502 --> 47:25.703
This isn't the piano, right?

47:25.705 --> 47:27.004
That's it.

47:27.006 --> 47:28.706
It ain't a Steinway.

47:28.708 --> 47:30.440
So what?

47:30.442 --> 47:33.276
Dr. Shirley only plays
on Steinway grand pianos.

47:33.278 --> 47:35.311
It's in his written contract.

47:35.313 --> 47:36.579
Who's Dr. Shirley?

47:36.581 --> 47:38.849
Dr. Shirley.
The Don Shirley Trio.

47:38.851 --> 47:40.718
They're playing tonight.

47:40.720 --> 47:42.452
Does it really matter?

47:42.454 --> 47:45.290
Yeah, it does.
It's in his contract.

47:46.591 --> 47:48.458
<font color="#ff00ff">(CHUCKLES)</font>: Come on, man.
Man, these coons

47:48.460 --> 47:50.529
can play on anything
you put in front of them.

47:54.667 --> 47:56.466
But it's a piece of shit.

47:56.468 --> 47:58.468
And there's garbage in there.

47:58.470 --> 48:00.370
So take it out.

48:00.372 --> 48:01.607
What'd you say?

48:02.709 --> 48:04.309
You heard me.

48:07.412 --> 48:09.512
Hey. You got two, three hours.

48:09.514 --> 48:11.548
Just get
a clean Steinway in here.

48:11.550 --> 48:13.617
Oh, there ain't a Steinway
on campus.

48:13.619 --> 48:15.418
Not my problem.

48:15.420 --> 48:16.821
<font color="#ff00ff">(SCOFFS)</font> I bet
there's not two Steinways

48:16.823 --> 48:18.488
in the whole state of Indiana.

48:18.490 --> 48:20.725
I guess you'd better move
your ass, then.

48:20.727 --> 48:22.762
Who you think you're
talking to, greaseball?

48:23.562 --> 48:25.495
<font color="#ff00ff">(MUSIC PLAYING)</font>

48:25.497 --> 48:27.564
<font color="#ff00ff">(WHIMPERING)</font>

48:27.566 --> 48:30.569
<font color="#ff00ff">(TRIO PLAYING UPBEAT SONG)</font>

48:43.783 --> 48:47.486
<font color="#ff00ff">(MUSIC PLAYING)</font>

48:52.725 --> 48:54.457
<font color="#ff8000">TONY</font>: <i>Dear Dolores:</i>

48:54.459 --> 48:56.526
<i>This morning
I had steak and eggs</i>

48:56.528 --> 48:57.795
<i>for breakfast.</i>

48:57.797 --> 49:01.799
<i>The band has been playing
at very ritzy joints.</i>

49:01.801 --> 49:04.101
<i>Dr. Shirley and I
are getting along pretty good.</i>

49:04.103 --> 49:06.837
<i>But sometimes
I think he gets sad,</i>

49:06.839 --> 49:09.405
<i>and that's why
he drinks too much.</i>

49:09.407 --> 49:12.810
<i>I never knew how very beautiful
this country was.</i>

49:12.812 --> 49:15.345
<i>Now that I'm seeing it, I know.</i>

49:15.347 --> 49:17.514
<i>You won't believe
how beautiful nature is.</i>

49:17.516 --> 49:19.817
<i>It is as beautiful as they say.</i>

49:19.819 --> 49:22.686
<i>And the traffic out here
in the country is nothing,</i>

49:22.688 --> 49:24.587
<i>which is fine by me.</i>

49:24.589 --> 49:27.625
<i>Right now I'm eating spaghetti
and meatballs in a diner</i>

49:27.627 --> 49:31.361
<i>that tastes like ketchup
on Chinese noodles.</i>

49:31.363 --> 49:32.595
<i>We are heading down south now.</i>

49:32.597 --> 49:35.900
<i>I will write you another letter
when we get down south.</i>

49:35.902 --> 49:38.636
<i>I love you. Your husband, Tony.</i>

49:38.638 --> 49:40.671
<i>P.S. Kiss the kids for me.</i>

49:40.673 --> 49:42.708
<font color="#ff00ff">(SONG ENDS)</font>
<font color="#ff00ff">(APPLAUSE)</font>

49:45.778 --> 49:49.579
<font color="#ff00ff">(ROCK AND ROLL PLAYING)</font>

49:49.581 --> 49:51.148
Got any family, Doc?

49:51.150 --> 49:52.683
Not really.

49:52.685 --> 49:55.453
Not really?
Either you do or you don't.

49:56.756 --> 49:58.823
It's a long story, Tony.

49:58.825 --> 50:01.992
What, we're in a hurry now?

50:01.994 --> 50:04.462
<font color="#ff00ff">(TURNS DOWN MUSIC)</font>
Let's hear it.

50:05.497 --> 50:07.597
I have a brother somewhere.

50:07.599 --> 50:10.567
We used to get together
once in a while,

50:10.569 --> 50:12.837
but it got more and more
difficult to stay in touch.

50:12.839 --> 50:16.173
Curse of being
a musician, I guess.

50:16.175 --> 50:18.609
Always on the road.

50:18.611 --> 50:20.711
Like a carnival worker.

50:20.713 --> 50:23.747
Hmm.
Or a criminal.

50:23.749 --> 50:26.416
Took quite the toll
on my marriage as well.

50:26.418 --> 50:28.018
You're married?
Was.

50:28.020 --> 50:29.954
June.

50:29.956 --> 50:31.789
Good person.

50:31.791 --> 50:33.991
Terrible grammar,
but a kind soul.

50:33.993 --> 50:35.893
You'd quite like her.

50:35.895 --> 50:37.493
June.

50:37.495 --> 50:39.632
Like, uh, like Lassie's mom.

50:41.499 --> 50:44.001
Unfortunately,
I couldn't do a husband act

50:44.003 --> 50:46.502
and a concert pianist act.

50:46.504 --> 50:49.507
Couldn't seem to manage
both worlds.

50:51.644 --> 50:53.811
<font color="#ff8000">TONY</font>: Kentucky Fried Chicken.

50:53.813 --> 50:55.511
In Kentucky!

50:55.513 --> 50:57.617
When's that ever gonna happen?

51:06.792 --> 51:08.591
<font color="#ff00ff">(CHUCKLES)</font>

51:08.593 --> 51:10.928
All right!

51:10.930 --> 51:12.630
Hey, you want some?

51:12.632 --> 51:14.632
I'm fine. Thank you, Tony.

51:14.634 --> 51:16.499
All right.

51:16.501 --> 51:20.804
Mmm. I think this is
the best Kentucky Fried Chicken

51:20.806 --> 51:22.740
I ever had.

51:22.742 --> 51:24.775
Probably 'cause it's fresher
down here, right?

51:24.777 --> 51:27.543
I don't think I've ever met
anyone with your appetite.

51:27.545 --> 51:29.914
No. I got the bucket
so you could have some.

51:29.916 --> 51:32.783
I've never had fried chicken
in my life.

51:32.785 --> 51:34.752
Who you bullshitting?

51:34.754 --> 51:36.654
You people love
the fried chicken,

51:36.656 --> 51:38.756
the grits
and the collard greens.

51:38.758 --> 51:41.557
I love it, too.
Negro cooks used to make it

51:41.559 --> 51:43.694
all the time
when I was in the Army.

51:43.696 --> 51:46.096
You have a very narrow
assessment of me, Tony.

51:46.098 --> 51:48.732
Yeah, right? I'm good.

51:48.734 --> 51:51.035
No. No, you're not good.
You're bad.

51:51.037 --> 51:53.070
I'm saying, just because
other Negroes enjoy

51:53.072 --> 51:55.739
certain types of music,
it doesn't mean I have to.

51:55.741 --> 51:58.574
Nor do we all eat the same kind of food.
Whoa.

51:58.576 --> 51:59.910
Wait a minute.

51:59.912 --> 52:01.912
If you said
all guineas like pizza

52:01.914 --> 52:04.114
and spaghetti and meatballs,
I'm not gonna get insulted.

52:04.116 --> 52:05.849
You're missing the point.

52:05.851 --> 52:07.985
For you to make the assumption
that every Negro...

52:07.987 --> 52:10.087
Hey, you want some or not?
No.

52:10.089 --> 52:11.855
Here. Come on.

52:11.857 --> 52:13.657
Tell me that don't smell good.
It...

52:13.659 --> 52:15.558
Huh?
It smells okay.

52:15.560 --> 52:18.729
I prefer not to get grease
on my blanket.

52:18.731 --> 52:20.864
<font color="#ff00ff">(MOCKING)</font> Ooh, I'm gonna get
grease on my blankey.

52:20.866 --> 52:22.900
Come on, have a piece.
It ain't gonna kill you.

52:22.902 --> 52:24.735
Come on, take it, eat it.
No.

52:24.737 --> 52:26.870
Take it.
I'm throwing it in the back.

52:26.872 --> 52:29.006
You... Don't you dare.
Then you better take it.

52:29.008 --> 52:31.742
How? Do you have plates
or utensils?

52:31.744 --> 52:33.110
<font color="#ff00ff">(SPEAKS ITALIAN)</font>
Eat it with your hands!

52:33.112 --> 52:34.878
That's how you're supposed to.
I can't do that.

52:34.880 --> 52:36.613
Eat it. Come on.
Take it, take it, take it.

52:36.615 --> 52:38.015
I gotta drive.
Ten and two on the wheel.

52:38.017 --> 52:39.683
Come on. Take it, take it, take it.
Tony...

52:39.685 --> 52:40.884
<font color="#ff00ff">(SHIRLEY GROANS)</font>
Come on, come on.

52:40.886 --> 52:42.886
There you go.

52:42.888 --> 52:44.755
Huh?

52:44.757 --> 52:46.623
I-I can't do this, Tony.

52:46.625 --> 52:48.792
Eat the goddamn thing!

52:48.794 --> 52:50.763
Jesus.

52:52.965 --> 52:55.067
<font color="#ff00ff">(ROCK AND ROLL SONG PLAYING
FAINTLY OVER RADIO)</font>

53:00.773 --> 53:03.173
What, no good?
Mm.

53:03.175 --> 53:06.045
<font color="#ff00ff">(MUSIC PLAYING)</font>

53:07.780 --> 53:10.748
It just seems...

53:10.750 --> 53:13.050
so un... unsanitary.

53:13.052 --> 53:14.918
Who gives a shit?

53:14.920 --> 53:17.054
Just relax and enjoy it.

53:17.056 --> 53:20.090
You know,
my father used to say...

53:20.092 --> 53:22.826
"Whatever you do,
do it a hundred percent."

53:22.828 --> 53:25.763
When you work, work.
When you laugh, laugh.

53:25.765 --> 53:28.999
When you eat,
eat like it's your last meal.

53:29.001 --> 53:30.801
You want another piece?

53:30.803 --> 53:32.636
Here. Have a breast.

53:32.638 --> 53:33.873
Delicious.

53:35.041 --> 53:36.840
Take it. Here you go.

53:36.842 --> 53:39.076
What do we do about the bones?

53:39.078 --> 53:41.145
<font color="#ff00ff">(MUSIC PLAYING)</font>

53:41.147 --> 53:43.082
We do this.

53:44.917 --> 53:46.216
This is what we do.

53:46.218 --> 53:48.118
<i><font color="#ffff00">♪</font> If you go to New Orleans</i>

53:48.120 --> 53:51.023
<i><font color="#ffff00">♪</font> You ought to go see
the Mardi Gras <font color="#ffff00">♪</font></i>

53:53.993 --> 53:55.726
There you go.

53:55.728 --> 53:57.061
<font color="#ff00ff">(BOTH LAUGHING)</font>

53:57.063 --> 53:59.963
<i><font color="#ffff00">♪</font> You ought to go see
the Mardi Gras <font color="#ffff00">♪</font></i>

53:59.965 --> 54:02.032
<font color="#ff00ff">(CHUCKLES)</font>

54:02.034 --> 54:05.104
<i><font color="#ffff00">♪</font> When you see
the Mardi Gras... <font color="#ffff00">♪</font></i>

54:06.405 --> 54:07.971
<font color="#ff8000">TONY</font>: What's the big deal, Doc?

54:07.973 --> 54:09.640
The squirrels
would've ate it anyway.

54:09.642 --> 54:10.841
<font color="#ff8000">SHIRLEY</font>: Pick it up, Tony.

54:10.843 --> 54:12.142
<font color="#ff8000">TONY</font>: Nature takes
care of the Earth.

54:12.144 --> 54:13.844
Pick it up.
Aw, geez.

54:13.846 --> 54:16.715
<i><font color="#ffff00">♪</font> If you wanna go
through New Orleans... <font color="#ffff00">♪</font></i>

54:25.925 --> 54:27.925
<font color="#ff00ff">(TONY GRUNTS)</font>

54:27.927 --> 54:29.159
<font color="#ff00ff">(INDISTINCT CHATTER)</font>

54:29.161 --> 54:30.729
<font color="#ff00ff">(DOOR SLAMS)</font>

54:34.900 --> 54:36.967
<font color="#ff00ff">(TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWING
IN DISTANCE)</font>

54:36.969 --> 54:38.737
<font color="#ff00ff">(CAT MEOWS)</font>

54:44.276 --> 54:45.878
<font color="#ff00ff">(CAT MEOWS)</font>

54:47.713 --> 54:49.882
This can't be right.

54:51.851 --> 54:53.851
It says right here,

54:53.853 --> 54:57.087
"Cozy as your own home."

54:57.089 --> 54:59.256
Place looks like my ass.

54:59.258 --> 55:01.792
This is the place.

55:01.794 --> 55:03.195
<font color="#ff00ff">(CAT GROWLS)</font>

55:04.697 --> 55:06.165
<font color="#ff00ff">(SIGHS HEAVILY)</font>

55:07.199 --> 55:09.201
The square one, please.

55:10.703 --> 55:13.105
Just this one?
Thank you.

55:15.975 --> 55:17.774
Hey, uh...

55:17.776 --> 55:19.743
if you need anything,

55:19.745 --> 55:22.146
I'll be right up the street
at the Easton Inn.

55:22.148 --> 55:24.148
Thank you, Tony.

55:24.150 --> 55:26.783
<font color="#ff00ff">(MUSIC PLAYING)</font>
<font color="#ff00ff">(INDISTINCT CHATTER)</font>

55:26.785 --> 55:27.951
<font color="#ff00ff">(DOG BARKING)</font>

55:27.953 --> 55:30.921
Hey, Floyd, we ready.
I told you,

55:30.923 --> 55:34.126
I can't play. My shoulder.
You and that damn shoulder.

55:35.294 --> 55:36.793
Hey!

55:36.795 --> 55:38.095
Hey, fancy-pants.

55:38.097 --> 55:39.796
You want to play?

55:39.798 --> 55:41.198
I beg your pardon?

55:41.200 --> 55:43.035
Come on, brother,
we short a man.

55:44.069 --> 55:45.804
Oh, I-I'd rather not.

55:46.939 --> 55:48.906
What, you too high and mighty?

55:48.908 --> 55:51.208
<font color="#ff8000">OTHER MAN</font>: No, no,
let him alone, let him alone.

55:51.210 --> 55:54.077
He just afraid of getting that
butler uniform a little dusty.

55:54.079 --> 55:55.812
Mm.

55:55.814 --> 55:58.148
I'm just, um...

55:58.150 --> 56:01.885
I'm on my way to meet a friend.

56:01.887 --> 56:04.123
Yeah, well, thanks for nothing.

56:05.324 --> 56:07.925
<font color="#ff00ff">(MEN LAUGHING)</font>
Floyd, come on, man.

56:07.927 --> 56:10.229
Shut your ass up, man,
and leave me alone!

56:13.232 --> 56:15.701
<font color="#ff00ff">(MUSIC PLAYING)</font>

56:19.872 --> 56:21.273
<font color="#ff00ff">(GROANS)</font>

56:25.544 --> 56:27.244
<font color="#ff00ff">(SIGHS)</font>

56:27.246 --> 56:28.881
<font color="#ff00ff">(SNIFFS)</font>

